{
	"_comment": "THE RUIN — a companion-as-actor puzzle world (Rung 5). Built long ago to be worked by a person AND their bonded companion together. SOUTH→NORTH you pass: the THRESHOLD (a slab barred by a buried weight-plate only the companion's search uncovers), the WARREN (the way caved in — four alike gaps in the rubble, and only the companion's nose knows which goes through), the CISTERN (a dark chamber — nothing tells you what's wrong; you must infer it needs LIGHT, kindle the dead ember, and send your companion to carry the mote to the cold brazier, which lights the murals and opens the way), and the SANCTUM beyond (the way home). See docs/puzzle-world-the-ruin-design.md. Coordinates are world-space pixels; colours are [r,g,b] 0..1. The 'ruin' block describes the pair-operated WARDS; ward state is SERVER-AUTHORITATIVE (shared). Slabs/nooks/braziers are interactables so world_art draws them and Solids blocks them.",
	"world_id": "the-ruin",
	"_regions_comment": "Named AREAS for new-area discovery (a bond source). threshold (arrival, south) → warren (the caved-in middle) → cistern (the dark chamber) → sanctum (the calm reward, north). The controller darkens the screen while you're in the 'cistern' region and its light-ward is unlit — the cue that makes you NAME the need.",
	"regions": [
