	"_border_comment": "A dense, jittered ring of old trees crowding the ruin's edge, so the place feels enclosed and overgrown rather than ending at the void. Presentation + colliders both come from this (seeded, identical every run).",
	"border": {"ring": true, "spacing": 70, "inset": 14, "jitter": 16, "rows": 3, "row_gap": 36},
	"_collision_comment": "Tall props block by default; the slabs, the ruined-wall columns, the rubble/nook wall, and the cistern gate set 'solid' explicitly with their own radii. The brazier, ember and murals are NOT solid (you and the companion move freely among them). body_radius/margin are the character size + a small standoff.",
	"collision": {"tree_radius": 9, "great_tree_radius": 16, "pond_blocks": true, "body_radius": 6, "margin": 2},
	"ground_color": [0.34, 0.4, 0.32],
	"_atmosphere_comment": "Dim, cool, mossy and enclosed. day_tint a cool green wash; a strong vignette closes the walls in; sparse pale motes drift like spores in shafts of light; the ground is mottled moss.",
