	"_ruin_comment": "The pair-operated WARDS, server-authoritative (shared). A ward links found+occupied → open (latched). threshold_gate: a buried PLATE the search uncovers → the slab. warren_passage: the TRUE nook (its 'slab') among 'decoys' the nose dismisses. cistern_light: a LIGHT-ward — it has a 'source' (the ember) and a 'brazier_id'/'murals'. The client treats KINDLING the ember (examining it) as the ward's 'uncover' (found), then on Go look the companion CARRIES the mote from the source to the plate (the brazier); arriving there is the 'occupy' (delivery) that opens the gate, lights the brazier, reveals the murals, and lifts the dark. The server only tracks found/open; the kindle, carry, murals and gloom are all client-side.",
	"ruin": {"wards": [{"id": "threshold_gate", "slab_id": "threshold_slab", "plate": [-120, 220], "uncover_radius": 120, "occupy_radius": 34, "latch": true, "hint": "The slab won't budge. Maybe your companion can find what works it — try sending it to look."}, {"id": "warren_passage", "slab_id": "warren_nook_c", "plate": [60, -300], "uncover_radius": 42, "occupy_radius": 38, "latch": true, "decoys": [[-180, -300], [-60, -300], [180, -300]], "hint": "Four gaps in the rubble, all alike — you can't tell which goes through. Your companion's nose can. Send it to look, and trust where it leads."}, {"id": "cistern_light", "slab_id": "cistern_gate", "plate": [0, -440], "occupy_radius": 40, "latch": true, "source": [-200, -380], "source_id": "cistern_ember", "brazier_id": "cistern_brazier", "region": "cistern", "murals": ["mural_l", "mural_r", "mural_gate"], "hint": "Pitch dark, and the door is sealed. Nothing here moves — but the brazier is cold and the ember is dead. This place needs LIGHT. Wake the ember, then send your companion to carry it."}, {"id": "paired_hall", "slab_id": "hall_door", "plates": ["a", "b"], "latch": true, "occupy_radius": 44, "region": "paired_hall", "plate_a": [-140, -720], "plate_b": [140, -720], "plate_a_id": "hall_plate_a", "plate_b_id": "hall_plate_b", "wedge_id": "hall_wedge", "hint": "This hall was built for TWO — two plates, and the great door yields only while BOTH bear weight at once. With a friend, a companion to each. Alone, jam the loose wedge onto one plate (examine it beside that plate) to hold it, then send your companion to stand the other."}]},
	"_portals_comment": "ruin_entry is where you arrive from the Vale (and step back through to leave); ruin_exit, in the sanctum beyond the lit gate, leads home.",
	"portals": [
		{"id": "ruin_entry", "type": "portal", "position": [0, 940], "color": [0.66, 0.72, 0.62], "label": "the way back out", "target_world": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111", "target_portal": "vale_ruin_portal", "arrival_offset": [0, -60]},
		{"id": "ruin_exit", "type": "portal", "position": [0, -1000], "color": [0.74, 0.66, 0.96], "label": "a shimmering portal", "target_world": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111", "target_portal": "vale_ruin_portal"}
	],
